RATIONALE

Video editor's are embarrassingly bug, especially when the
size of the project grows.

Rendering takes a long time, with this approach you can
leverage the power of Make.

Source control friendly.


FORMAT

The utilities use raw RGBA video, parameters for ffmpeg are:

	-f rawvideo
	-pix_fmt rgba
	-s:v ${WIDTH}x${HEIGHT}
	-r ${FRAME_RATE}
